    • Enum Constant Detail

      • SUCCESS

        public static final Job.Result SUCCESS
        Indicates that Job.onRunJob(Params) was successful.

      • FAILURE

        public static final Job.Result FAILURE
        Indicates that Job.onRunJob(Params) failed, but the Job shouldn't be rescheduled.

        Periodic jobs will continue to run. The failure count of the job is incremented, what can be helpful in the next interval.
        See Also:
        Job.Params.getFailureCount()

      • RESCHEDULE

        public static final Job.Result RESCHEDULE
        Indicates that Job.onRunJob(Params) failed and the Job should be rescheduled with the defined back-off criteria. Note that returning RESCHEDULE for a periodic Job is invalid and ignored.

        Returning RESCHEDULE for periodic jobs has the same effect as returning FAILURE.
